segments.text: What kind of emails do you receive about your work?
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: I receive a lot of emails from my higher ups.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: So my manager, people from other departments as well, usually following up for things, um, or scheduling meetings.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: Um, just a lot of work that needs to be done and reminders to please do this work.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: So do you normally reply to emails as soon as you receive them?
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: Um, I don't because I feel like there's no point in replying if the work hasn't been done.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: So let's say we're supposed to schedule a meeting and something needs to be done.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: I'd much prefer to get that thing done and then respond by saying, okay, here it is.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: Here's the file that you, um, that you requested or that you asked for.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: And, um, yeah, instead of, you know, uh, random sort of hello, well received.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: Are you happy to receive emails that are advertising things?
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_01

segments.text: No, I don't think anyone would be.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00

segments.text: Unless it's for a brand that I follow or that I like, unless they're having a sale.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_00
